	<text>
		<body>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Columbus Ga</placeName> <date>Sept 8th 1867</date></p>
				<p>Rev Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Your esteemed note enclosed<lb/> in the package of Books was duly received<lb/> allow me to thank you for myself &#38;  wife<lb/> for your kind greetings &#38;  <sic>wel</sic> wishes and<lb/> I trust the day may not be far distant when<lb/> we will become acquainted with each other<lb/> &#8220;a la personel&#8221;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Enclosed I hand you a post office<lb/> draft for the prayer Books &#38;  Almanacs say<lb/> &#36;7.75 the other Books I am sorry to<lb/> say I had to turn over to <persName>I. I. Moses<lb/> Esq.</persName> agreeable to your direction as I did<lb/> purchase copies of all three of those of <persName>Miss<lb/> Bloch &#38;  Co.</persName> of <placeName>Cincinnati</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">My wife unites with me in wishing<lb/> you many happy years and begs me to<lb/> remember her kindly to you.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I am Rev Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">very Respectfully</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">Samuel Meyer</persName></p>
		</body>
